{"version":"0.4","title":"special training","type":"page","content":[{"id":"34d8c9d6","settings":[],"elements":[{"id":"502618d5","settings":{"_column_size":100,"_inline_size":null},"elements":[{"id":"19b587b1","settings":{"title":"NAVODAYA SPECIAL TRAINING ","header_size":"h3","align":"center","title_color":"#2D5160"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"column"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"section"},{"id":"70709045","settings":[],"elements":[{"id":"7157d390","settings":{"_column_size":100,"_inline_size":null},"elements":[{"id":"27f109ab","settings":{"image":{"url":"https:\/\/34e.d37.myftpupload.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image4.jpg","id":356}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"image","elType":"widget"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"column"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"section"},{"id":"6a1df3d3","settings":[],"elements":[{"id":"7d2e5f09","settings":{"_column_size":100,"_inline_size":null},"elements":[{"id":"37867d73","settings":{"editor":"<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Obtain a good book-&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"background: none;\">Very much required as it clearly guides you what sort of questions you are going to deal with rather than wondering here and there clueless.<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Train to practice daily-&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"background: none;\">This might sound like a cliche but believe me competitive exams demands regular practice even if it is JNVST. Ask the student to sit for at least 2 hours with the questions. Here, I am assuming that student has to attend school and has to complete school homework as well.<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Make language portion fun-&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"background: none;\">Language part is actually fun as it merely consists of small stories. Prepare student to take it in this way only. Tell him\/her to enjoy the stories.<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Handle mathematics with care-&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"background: none;\">This part makes a lot of difference as the most students are bored of maths. Have patience with maths and try to take it in parts with more interesting parts (language and aptitude).<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Make aptitude part a game-&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"background: none;\">Many teachers try to force aptitude abilities but believe me it takes time to develop aptitude. In our case, this is the major part of all. So, it becomes more important to tackle this one with utmost care. Challenge your student to complete some exercises.<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Teach time management-<\/span><span style=\"background: none;\">&nbsp;Time management is really important as question paper is quite lengthy for the students of 5th std. Students in that age are taught to write everything on paper. For example, while solving questions from unitary method they would write-<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">Cost of one pen = Rs. a<\/span><\/p><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgb(40, 40, 41); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; background: none;\">So, cost of 10 pens = Rs. a x 10<\/span><\/p>"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"column"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"section"}]}